id: pmc-w8iu
title: Bump @types/node to ^25.9.1 and rewire CI to full-history changelog
description: Pick up latest @types/node minor and switch release.yml to --mode replace --all-release-tags --version for deterministic CHANGELOG.md regeneration on every release run.
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: changelog,ci,deps,typescript
created_at: "2026-05-25T20:48:54.973Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-25T20:49:09.050Z"
deadline: "2026-05-26T20:00:00.000Z"
assignee: claude
author: claude
estimated_minutes: 30
acceptance_criteria: "@types/node ^25.9.1 installed, release workflow uses --all-release-tags with pending --version flag, RELEASE_NOTES.md is windowed to the new release tag."
parent: pmc-9mck
release: v2026.05.25-1
resolution: fixed
expected_result: deps and CI changes committed; release pipeline produces full-history CHANGELOG.md and per-release GitHub release notes
actual_result: package.json + release.yml updated; 31 unit tests still pass; npm audit shows 0 vulnerabilities
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pmc-9mck,related,"2026-05-25T20:48:54.973Z",null,null
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-25T20:48:54.973Z",claude,Picked up after npm view confirmed 25.9.1 latest.
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-25T20:48:54.973Z",claude,"package.json now also exposes changelog:full for local full-history rebuilds and changelog:check uses replace mode to catch drift."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-25T20:48:54.973Z",claude,"GitHub release notes should use --since-previous-tag/--until-release-tag windowing so the release body shows just the new tag's changes, while the committed CHANGELOG.md shows the full history."
